commit.message: update gh actions to use checkout v3

Revert "Add a test to check without B::COW"

This partially reverts commit 7d9c699e962494fcdf7fd0c929c86195b29cb40f.

Optionally depending on B::COW is extra complexity, which was added
because it would not always be installed as a prereq. The issue with
B::COW not being seen as a prereq was due to the Makefile.PL not
including compatibilty code for older EUMM versions. This has been
fixed, so the module should always be available.

switch CI tests to install using cpanm to properly pick up prereqs

cpm can only install from a cpanfile, META file, or a fixed list of
prereqs. We want to install the prereqs from the Makefile.PL file, which
cpanm will do for us.

The install-with-cpanm sudo option is rather broken. It runs the cpanm
command itself with sudo, which means any files generated, like
MYMETA.json, are owned by root. This will prevent later commands from
working properly. cpanm's own sudo option is fine though, since it only
runs the install action with sudo.

At some point this should be changed prepare a dist dir or dist archive.
A dist dir or archive would contain a META file, allowing cpm to work.
It would make it easier to switch to a different author tool, and test on
a system or perl that can't run that author tool.

maybe less sudo?

fix test prereqs being ignored on older ExtUtils::MakeMaker

Old versions of ExtUtils::MakeMaker don't support TEST_REQUIRES or
BUILD_REQUIRES. Check for the older versions, and fold the prereqs into
supported parameters.
update Test::More prereq to 0.88 for done_testing
use correct license name
update MANIFEST file
remove .travis.yml

remove out of date META.yml

There is little reason to keep a META file in the repository, as it will
be generated when making a release. And the META.yml file was out of
date and incorrect.
